<center><div style="padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-left: 3px solid white; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; background: #00000050;>
----
<center>
=== Description - The Rose Gardens===
</center>
If you are viewing this document, you have successfully managed to no-clip into the Concrete Terraces (Level 543)! Right now, you are standing within the Rose Gardens. Though it is easy to get lost in the flower-strewn labyrinth, fret not — the non-Euclidean geometry present in most [[Levels|other levels]] is absent here. The level itself is a large concrete structure filled with various flora, including flowers, vines, moss, and other vegetation, though how exactly these grow is unknown, as the level lacks any soil whatsoever. Due to this, it is theorized that the plants may not even be real, or artificial turfs of some sort.

The spaces between the hallways are large classrooms of varying appearance and layout, though always containing the same flowers present on the ground below. It is worth noting that the smell of flowers permeates the entire level, regardless of your position; though, strangely, the flowers covering the floor lack any scent whatsoever. Windows line the hallways, though they seemingly lead to nowhere — as studies show that what is behind the windows may not actually be there, not unlike [[Level 4]]. In addition, the faint sounds of running water and birds chirping may be heard, though none have ever been recorded.

In lieu of the typical disorienting hum-buzz you may hear from the level's fluorescent lights, the noise is instead replaced with a faint harmonic tune or rhythmic hum, though this depends on the area you may be in. Strangely, however, the overhead fluorescent lights are not turned on at all — the bright lights outside are the only prominent source of illumination. Level 543 may be suspended possibly thousands of feet in the air, evidenced by a thick layer of cumulus clouds blanketing the sky at all times. The weather and climate are constant on the level, with clear skies and a cool temperature of 64 degrees Fahrenheit (18 degrees Celsius). 

The interiors of the classrooms are filled with items you may expect, such as desks, chairs, and a blackboard. In some rooms, essentials may be strewn throughout the desks, though the level contains a complete and utter lack of any food or [[Object 1|water]] whatsoever. Due to this, starvation is the only prevalent danger on Level 543, as there are no other hazards. Though the presence of stairwells imply the existence of layers beyond the ground floor, it is worth note that these stairwells are entirely inaccessible, their doors locked at all times. Due to this, the only effective method of exploration is linear travel, though this is often sluggish as well due to the uneven terrain.

----
</div></center>


