<center><div style="padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-left: 3px solid white; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; background: #00000050;>
----
<center>
=== Description - Deeper regions===
</center>

The deeper regions of Level 543 are occupied by large, dilapidated mall complexes. These areas, unlike the rest of the level, more closely resemble commercial areas, with most surfaces being made up of drywall and plaster rather than the omnipresent concrete. Other identifiable features include sparsely placed pillars, dysfunctional fluorescent lights, and brick pathways that interconnect rooms. 

In the deeper regions, the undergrowth is more concentrated, the grass and flowers growing far denser than usual. Grass and small flora sprout through cracks in the flooring, reaching ankle height in some areas, while clusters of wildflowers bloom in irregular patterns along the walls and ceilings. Despite this, the level's signature roses are still present along the floor, covering most surfaces. Additionally, in lieu of the rose smell, the scent of damp earth permeates the entire region, present regardless of your position. 

Though shops are certainly present, they are hollowed out, with shattered display windows, splintered wooden counters, and toppled shelves scattered across the floors. The interconnecting brick pathways are usually covered in moss and leaves, weaving between different rooms — though most lead to nowhere. The mall areas notably have remarkably poor ventilation, with a viscous biomass-esque substance leaking out of the ventilation pipes and hatches along the walls. 

----
</div></center>

