<center><div style="padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-left: 3px solid white; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; background: #00000050;>
----
<center>
=== Description - Additional Information===
</center>

A strange phenomenon on Level 543 that you may experience is losing your track of time. All methods of timekeeping, be it watches, clocks, or otherwise, break upon entry and remain dysfunctional until exiting the level. Many wanderers have a reported a "distinct lack" of temporal awareness, as entire days, if not weeks can pass by after entry. Due to this, it is theorized that Level 543 contains a temporal anomaly that can significantly affect how time flows within the level to a considerable capacity. Therefore, it is possible to spend more time in the level than you may intend to, and thus be more prone to starvation or dehydration. 

In addition, Level 543 contains several smaller areas:

<tabber>
|-|Electrical Rooms=
Electrical rooms are the most common smaller area within Level 543, and are typically placed between large hallways. They are easily identifiable by the numerous (yet variable) amount of caution signs present on the door, haphazardly placed and sticked on in an almost frantic manner. The interiors of the electrical rooms are, surprisingly, bereft of most electrical equipment, rather being covered in a thick layer of wires that lead seemingly nowhere. The wires, though exposed, do not carry enough voltage to cause significant (if any) bodily harm to a person.
|-|Storage Halls=
Storage halls, though scarce, may be found in larger, more open areas, indicated by large, yet unmovable metal doors. Strangely, the storage halls seem to lack any resources whatsoever — filled with empty cardboard boxes atop tall, steel shelves. In addition, the amount of overgrowth present in the storage areas is notably more concentrated, with vines strewn across the walls and flora growing on most surfaces.
|-|Courtyards=
Courtyards are large, open areas between the level's separate hallways. In lieu of the flora you may expect to be present on the floor, it is rather replaced by an array of concrete tiles, variable in width, color, and texture. Though not present in every courtyard, they often contain a large, stone water fountain in the center, along with wooden benches and rubbish bins.
</tabber>

----
</div></center>


<center><div style="padding: 20px; margin: 20px; border-left: 3px solid white; text-align: justify; max-width: 800px; background: #00000050;>
----
<center>
=== Description - Entrances and Exits===
</center>
<center>
====Entrances====
</center>Level 543 contains six entrances, which are listed and detailed below for viewing convenience:

* One may access this level from [[Level 48]], by interacting with one of the many nutrition posters present in the stores;
* By no-clipping into flowers in [[Level 85]];
* By jumping out a window in [[Level 52]];
* By wandering far enough in [[Level 70]];
* By no-clipping into scarce flowers in [[Level 10]];
* And by resting in [[Level 997]].
It is additionally worth note that there may be an additional, omnipresent access point to Level 543. Many wanderers have reported ending up in Level 543 after a large fall, typically onto flowers, bushes, or other shrubbery. 

<center>
====Exits====
</center>

Likewise, Level 543 has five documented exits:

* Walking beyond the parameters of the deeper regions, which may take you to [[Level 13]];
* Jumping out a window, which may lead to [[Level 97]];
* No-clipping or interacting with a poster of a train, which leads to [[Level 61]]
* And interacting with the computers present in the classrooms, which lead one to [[Level 4]]. It is additionally worth note that tampering with the Microsoft Powerpoint application has a chance to lead to [[Level 60]] instead.<br />
* Rarely, deeper and darker regions of the level may transition to [[Level 399.1]].

----
</div></center>

